'''''Demolition Derby''''' is a [[racing game]] developed by [[Midway Games|Bally Midway]] and released as an [[arcade video game]] in 1985.<ref name="Akagi"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arcade-museum.com/game_detail.php?game_id=7551|title=Demolition Derby - Videogame by Bally Midway|website=www.arcade-museum.com}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
The player takes part in a [[demolition derby]]. Hit other cars in the [[Radiator (engine cooling)|radiator]] to damage them, while avoiding being hit in one's own radiator. [[Power-ups]] include wrenches, screwdrivers and car keys.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skooldays.com/categories/arcade/ag1192.htm|title=Demolition Derby (80's) : Old Memories|website=www.skooldays.com}}</ref>

A notable feature of the [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]] mode was the ability to enter a game while it is in progress; the message "CAR ENTERING DERBY" would appear on screen.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=d6wCEAAAQBAJ&q=%22Demolition+Derby%22+1984+bally&pg=PA287|title=Attract Mode: The Rise and Fall of Coin-Op Arcade Games|first=Jamie|last=Lendino|date=September 27, 2020|publisher=Steel Gear Press|via=Google Books}}</ref>

==Reception==
''Demolition Derby'' was listed in the book ''[[1001 Video Games You Must Play Before You Die]]''.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=olpPoAswgHoC&q=%22Demolition+Derby%22+1984+bally&pg=PT165|title=1001 Video Games You Must Play Before You Die: You Must Play Before You Die|first=Tony|last=Mott|date=December 5, 2011|publisher=Octopus|isbn=9781844037155|via=Google Books}}</ref>

